# Build artifacts that aren't covered above
*.log

# Bug-bounty / vulnerability disclosure drafts.
#
# The reports/ directory holds operator-authored disclosure drafts
# for active engagements. These describe specific, often UNPATCHED
# vulnerabilities in third-party software. Committing them to the
# public repo before the operator submits to the relevant bounty
# programme is a 0-day disclosure — it pre-discloses a live
# vulnerability, violates virtually every bug-bounty programme's
# coordinated-disclosure rules, and forfeits any payout. This
# ignore is load-bearing: keep it.
#
# If the operator wants to publish a report AFTER disclosure +
# patch release, they can move it out of reports/ or force-add it
# explicitly. The default must be "never committed."
reports/
